This paper is about training deep learning models for biomedical image segmentation using a new superpixel-based data augmentation method. The paper focuses on computer vision and machine learning techniques applied to biomedical images, which suggests that the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new data augmentation method, which falls under the category of machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also involves the use of deep learning models, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also mentions the use of 2D and 3D images, which suggests that cs.MM (Multimedia) could also be a relevant category. Finally, the paper involves the use of deep neural networks, which suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) could also be a relevant category.
